# C# Property Convention

Do not use auto-properties (`{ get; set; }`, `{ get; private set; }`, `{ get; }`).

Use a backing field and an expression-bodied property:

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
public string ActionName { get; }
public bool HasSelectedTarget { get; private set; }

// ✅ GOOD
readonly ActionData data;
public string ActionName => data.Id;

bool hasSelectedTarget;
public bool HasSelectedTarget => hasSelectedTarget;
```

- Use `readonly` fields when the value is set only in the constructor.
- Use plain fields for mutable state; assign the field inside the class, expose via `=>`.
- For structs, use `readonly` fields with expression-bodied properties.
